Route session notes through the Tier-1 regex classifier (ADR-072).

Walks a session file, computes `blake3(body)` for each note, applies the Tier-1 cascade, writes a sidecar under `.cosmon/state/sessions/.route/<sid>/<body_hash>.json`, and (when confidence warrants) nucleates a `temp:proposed` molecule via `cs nucleate`. Tiers 2–4 are future work; low-confidence notes are marked `tier4_pending` and escalate to the verdict-door.

Usage: cs session route [OPTIONS] [SESSION]

Arguments:
  [SESSION]
          Session file stem (e.g. `session-2026-04-22T10-31-31Z`) or an absolute path. When omitted, defaults to scanning every session file if `--all` is passed, or the currently-open session otherwise

Options:
      --all
          Process every session file under `.cosmon/state/sessions/`

      --config <PATH>
          Path to configuration file

      --dry-run
          Print what would be classified without writing sidecars or nucleating molecules

  -v, --verbose
          Enable verbose output

      --json
          Output in JSON format

      --no-stage
          Skip auto-nucleation of high-confidence `temp:proposed` molecules — write sidecars only. Useful when backfilling or debugging

      --max <MAX>
          Cap sidecars emitted this run (safety net for batch backfills)
          
          [default: 500]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
